{"id":"155","paper":{"title":{"text":"Sidestepping the Rayleigh limit for LoS MIMO: a distributed architecture for long-range wireless fiber "},"authors":[{"name":"Andrew Irish"},{"name":"Francois Quitin"},{"name":"Upamanyu Madhow"},{"name":"Mark Rodwell"}],"abstr":{"text":"The degrees of freedom in LoS spatial multiplexing are limited by the Rayleigh criterion: for fixed antenna separation (limited by node form factor) and carrier frequency (limited by regulation and available electronics), spatial multiplexing is available up to a range determined by the Rayleigh criterion.  In this paper, we propose a distributed architecture for sidestepping this criterion, synthesizing a full rank MIMO matrix  by using the natural geographic dispersion of relays between the transmitter and receiver .We focus specifically on the design of  �wireless fiber� links with data rates of 10-100 Gbps over ranges of tens of kilometers, exploiting, in additional to spatial multiplexing, the large beamforming gains and bandwidths available in the millimeter wave band."},"body":{"text":"j U\ni i\nj U\nj U\n2 1 2 1 1\nu u\nu u u u u u u\n∗ l\n∗ u\n∗∗ l\n∗∗ u\n∗∗ l\n∗∗ l\n∗∗ l\n∗∗ l\n∗∗ l\n1 max"},"refs":[]},"file":{"jsonClass":"File","file":"/home/arnfred/Code/trailhead/resources/ita2013/155"},"links":[{"id":"205","weight":4},{"id":"2760","weight":3},{"id":"1486","weight":6},{"id":"3180","weight":5},{"id":"67","weight":10},{"id":"2206","weight":2},{"id":"1606","weight":6},{"id":"153","weight":3},{"id":"3037","weight":6},{"id":"93","weight":2},{"id":"436","weight":7},{"id":"3191","weight":3},{"id":"12","weight":5},{"id":"223","weight":6},{"id":"1547","weight":4},{"id":"2254","weight":3},{"id":"1278","weight":7},{"id":"2287","weight":2},{"id":"3200","weight":3},{"id":"3083","weight":2},{"id":"2217","weight":2},{"id":"3222","weight":5},{"id":"2291","weight":4},{"id":"307","weight":7},{"id":"981","weight":3},{"id":"1430","weight":2},{"id":"3021","weight":2},{"id":"170","weight":3},{"id":"813","w